The paper deals with the problem of learning good trajectories for manipulation tasks, which is a core problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a co-active online learning framework for teaching robots the preferences of its users, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses theoretical regret bounds of the algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the preferences of users being influenced by the surrounding environment, which suggests the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper uses grocery checkout tasks as an example, which involves object recognition and manipulation, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) another possible category.
